I wrote a new - new game, for Narrascope's Game Jam (a Narrative Fiction weeklong meeting of people who write and consume it). It's 15,000 words, and has statistics and various things you can unlock.
I made this earlier, but forgot to post about it here. Time passes, heh. :p
But I'm proud of it - I wrote 10,000 words in 6 hours to get it finished under the deadline, and even though it shipped with massive bugs I fixed the bugs and have a playable game that I enjoy reading when I play it myself. That's all you can really ask for. :)
